                        "name": "Dance of Death",
                        "type": "offensive_action",
                        "text": "The necrophidius sways, its serpentine form undulating and clattering in a hypnotic rhythm. Each creature that witnesses the dance must attempt a DC 18 Will save. <br/><b>Critical Success</b> The creature is unaffected and is temporarily immune for 24 hours. <br/><b>Success</b> The creature is unnerved by the swaying and becomes <a aonid=\"16\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">flat-footed</a> until the end of the necrophidius's next turn. <br/><b>Failure</b> The creature is distracted by the swaying, becoming <a aonid=\"36\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">stunned 1</a>. After it recovers, it is flat-footed until the end of the necrophidius's next turn. <br/><b>Critical Failure</b> As failure, but stunned 3.",
